---
import ContactCTA from '../components/ContactCTA.astro';
import Hero from '../components/Hero.astro';
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About | Lorraine Sawicki" description="About Lorraine Sawicki — Technical Content Engineer, AI Engineer, and Creative Technologist based in San Francisco.">
	<div class="stack gap-20">
		<main class="wrapper about">
			<Hero
				title="About"
				tagline="Thanks for stopping by. Read below to learn more about myself and my background."
			>
				{/* <img
					width="1553"
					height="873"
					src="/assets/at-work.jpg"
					alt="Lorraine Sawicki at work with a colleague"
				/> */}
			</Hero>

			<section>
				<h2 class="section-title">Background</h2>
				<div class="content">
					<p>
						Lorraine Sawicki is a Technical Content Engineer, AI Engineer, and Creative Technologist
						with a B.S. in Computer Science and 15+ years of experience bridging engineering, design,
						and storytelling. She is an expert in Next.js, TypeScript, and AI prompt engineering, with
						a proven track record of building scalable systems for technical communication — from
						custom AWS serverless ML tools to complex digital taxonomies. Her career spans co-founding
						and running a web hosting company for a decade (grounding her in deep UNIX/Linux systems
						fundamentals), full-stack product engineering across startups and SaaS platforms, and most
						recently serving as Technical Program Manager at CadenceOneFive, a climate retrofit
						startup, where she translated regulatory complexity into actionable engineering work
						across a 900-ticket project landscape. She is adept at translating high-level
						infrastructure concepts into high-fidelity narratives that withstand senior engineering
						scrutiny, and passionate about treating content as an engineering discipline — through
						automation, reusable prompt libraries, LLM-integrated workflows, and context window
						management.
					</p>
					<p>
						Today Lorraine runs Rosehip Studio LLC, an independent San Francisco practice where
						technology meets design across nature, food, gardens, and the built environment. Her
						studio work includes What's Growing Here, a Supabase and Next.js plant cataloging platform
						for homeowners and landscapers; interactive data visualizations; and AI-assisted content
						pipelines for drafting, review, and publishing. A designer and illustrator as much as an
						engineer, she sketches buildings and parks, invents constructed languages, and brings a
						UX-informed, systems-first sensibility to everything she ships — believing the best
						technical work, like the best gardens, comes from understanding the whole ecosystem rather
						than just following instructions.
					</p>
					<p>
						Lorraine grew up on the outskirts of New York City. Early in her career she worked at the
						Brooklyn Museum, which shaped her understanding of art, curation, and exhibitions in a
						vibrant real-world setting. She took classes at the Art Students League of New York,
						studying life drawing and storytelling. Drawn to both nature and technology, her years
						living in Palm Beach Gardens, Seattle, and San Francisco deepened her perception of
						culture through direct lived experience. She has served as an art docent at two elementary
						schools.
					</p>
				</div>
			</section>
			{/* Education and Skills sections removed for now — restore from git history when ready */}
		</main>

		<ContactCTA />
	</div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
	.about {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 3.5rem;
	}

	img {
		margin-top: 1.5rem;
		border-radius: 1.5rem;
		box-shadow: var(--shadow-md);
	}

	section {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 0.5rem;
		color: var(--gray-200);
	}

	.section-title {
		grid-column-start: 1;
		font-size: var(--text-xl);
		color: var(--gray-0);
	}

	.content {
		grid-column: 2 / 4;
	}

	.content :global(a) {
		text-decoration: 1px solid underline transparent;
		text-underline-offset: 0.25em;
		transition: text-decoration-color var(--theme-transition);
	}

	.content :global(a:hover),
	.content :global(a:focus) {
		text-decoration-color: currentColor;
	}

	@media (min-width: 50em) {
		.about {
			display: grid;
			grid-template-columns: 1fr 60% 1fr;
		}

		.about > :global(:first-child) {
			grid-column-start: 2;
		}

		section {
			display: contents;
			font-size: var(--text-lg);
		}
	}
</style>
